1
00:02:43,730 --> 00:02:45,061
Come on.

2
00:02:46,533 --> 00:02:47,700
This is ridiculous.

3
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:50,567
What is the deal
with these people?

4
00:02:54,741 --> 00:02:56,676
KCBG.
Who are you holding for?

5
00:02:56,676 --> 00:02:59,312
Listen, I've been trying
to get ahold of Lori Tanner...

6
00:02:59,312 --> 00:03:00,880
for the last ten minutes.

7
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:03,116
I'm sorry. She's not picking up
in her office right now.

8
00:03:03,116 --> 00:03:06,119
Yeah, well, tell her
she just lost her story.

9
00:03:06,119 --> 00:03:08,488
Hold on. Maybe she's
somewhere else in the building.

10
00:03:08,488 --> 00:03:10,290
Let me try and locate her.

11
00:03:10,290 --> 00:03:14,027
Wrinkle-free dirt-repellent
polyester...

12
00:03:14,027 --> 00:03:15,895
Is this working for you so far?

13
00:03:15,895 --> 00:03:19,832
Is trying to make a comeback
from the disco decade.

14
00:03:19,832 --> 00:03:22,936
Edit bay one.

15
00:03:22,936 --> 00:03:24,571
Yeah, hold on a second.

16
00:03:24,571 --> 00:03:27,907
...is finding new life
among top clothing designers.

17
00:03:27,907 --> 00:03:31,611
Hi, this is Judy Sanders
over at Emax.

18
00:03:31,611 --> 00:03:34,614
Oh, God, Judy!
Thanks for calling me back.

19
00:03:34,614 --> 00:03:36,616
It's not my fault we're stuck
with this lightweight...

20
00:03:36,616 --> 00:03:38,418
Shh! It's important.

21
00:03:38,418 --> 00:03:39,919
I didn't expect
to hear from you again.

22
00:03:39,919 --> 00:03:44,090
Look, I can sneak you
into the lab tomorrow night...

23
00:03:44,090 --> 00:03:46,192
if you've still got
that five hundred you promised.

24
00:03:46,192 --> 00:03:48,228
Yeah, yeah.
I just have to make sure...

25
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:49,429
you can get me in
to see the animals.

26
00:03:49,429 --> 00:03:51,331
I got to know exactly
what's being done to them.

27
00:03:51,331 --> 00:03:52,498
No problem.

28
00:03:52,498 --> 00:03:55,835
Why don't you meet me
at 8:30 at the north gate?

29
00:03:55,835 --> 00:03:58,404
And don't be late. I can't
afford to get in trouble.

30
00:03:58,404 --> 00:04:01,274
I'll be there.

31
00:04:01,274 --> 00:04:03,367
Yes! Yes!

32
00:04:11,951 --> 00:04:14,153
Good morning, Mr. Perez.

33
00:04:14,153 --> 00:04:16,022
Buenas dias, Senor Perez.

34
00:04:16,022 --> 00:04:18,616
Buenas dias, Senor Perez.

35
00:04:20,426 --> 00:04:22,629
How are you, Mrs. Perez?

36
00:04:22,629 --> 00:04:25,331
Como esta usted, Senora Perez?

37
00:04:25,331 --> 00:04:28,425
Como esta usted, senora?

38
00:04:29,869 --> 00:04:32,238
How are you, Miss Perez?

39
00:04:32,238 --> 00:04:34,807
Como esta usted,
Senorita Perez?

40
00:04:34,807 --> 00:04:36,900
Como esta... shut up!

41
00:04:38,745 --> 00:04:41,748
- Hello, sir.
- Hola, senor.

42
00:04:41,748 --> 00:04:44,517
Hola, senor.

43
00:04:44,517 --> 00:04:46,819
- Hello, madame.
- Hola, senora.

44
00:04:46,819 --> 00:04:48,650
Hola, sen...

45
00:04:51,557 --> 00:04:53,616
Ladies and gentlemen.

46
00:04:56,729 --> 00:04:59,265
I am pleased to meet you.

47
00:04:59,265 --> 00:05:01,426
Mucho gusto en conocerle.

48
00:05:04,637 --> 00:05:07,162
- Thank you.
- Gracias.

49
00:05:09,976 --> 00:05:12,274
- Please.
- Por favor.

50
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,911
- Goodbye.
- Adios.

51
00:05:44,911 --> 00:05:47,513
This is exactly the type
of story I've been looking for.

52
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:49,349
What do you know
about animal rights?

53
00:05:49,349 --> 00:05:50,983
You have a parrot
that can't stand you.

54
00:05:50,983 --> 00:05:52,685
It's topical. It's hard-hitting.

55
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:54,520
I think I can do something
significant with it.

56
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:56,823
Do an expose. Who knows
what goes on in that place?

57
00:05:56,823 --> 00:05:59,192
We're already running late
on the polyester segment.

58
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:01,327
Polyester segment.
Please, give me a break.

59
00:06:01,327 --> 00:06:03,162
Drip-dry suits.
That's real hard-core.

60
00:06:03,162 --> 00:06:06,866
Excuse me, but that's what
we get paid to do around here.

61
00:06:06,866 --> 00:06:08,634
How many times
have we had this discussion...

62
00:06:08,634 --> 00:06:11,938
about what we'd do if we got
a chance to cover a real story?

63
00:06:11,938 --> 00:06:14,073
No, I'm not going to let you
do this to me again.

64
00:06:14,073 --> 00:06:15,975
You've got to shoot this one
for me, Annie. You're the best.

65
00:06:15,975 --> 00:06:18,044
Why can't we be
like everybody else, huh?

66
00:06:18,044 --> 00:06:20,813
It doesn't make sense to shoot
the whole story on spec.

67
00:06:20,813 --> 00:06:22,949
We should just sell everybody
on the idea first.

68
00:06:22,949 --> 00:06:25,752
No! Because they'll just go
and put somebody else on it.

69
00:06:25,752 --> 00:06:28,121
The only way we're ever gonna
get to do anything real here...

70
00:06:28,121 --> 00:06:31,724
is if we just shoot the story
and blow their socks off.

71
00:06:31,724 --> 00:06:34,090
I'm doing this
with or without you.

72
00:06:45,938 --> 00:06:47,530
Come on. Bring it up.

73
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:54,547
What is the deal? It's 9:00.

74
00:06:54,547 --> 00:06:57,283
What's her name... Judy... said
she'd meet us here at 8:30.

75
00:06:57,283 --> 00:06:58,682
Maybe we should just
get out of here.

76
00:07:00,286 --> 00:07:02,379
There's no answer. Damn it.

77
00:07:05,124 --> 00:07:06,659
What are you doing?

78
00:07:06,659 --> 00:07:08,294
I'm sneaking in.

79
00:07:08,294 --> 00:07:10,863
Lori.

80
00:07:10,863 --> 00:07:12,432
Lori!

81
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:13,558
Wait.

82
00:07:17,503 --> 00:07:18,731
Lori, wait for me.

83
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:22,975
Did your wife fix me up
with her sister yet or what?

84
00:07:22,975 --> 00:07:26,512
On second thought, I don't think
that's such a good idea.

85
00:07:26,512 --> 00:07:30,550
I found out she won't be
turning 18 for another 8 months.

86
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:32,852
Hey, that's perfect, man.

87
00:07:32,852 --> 00:07:35,822
If I was you,
I'd rewrite that personal ad.

88
00:07:35,822 --> 00:07:36,989
Oh, come on, man.

89
00:07:36,989 --> 00:07:39,158
I haven't gotten a date
from that personal ad.

90
00:07:39,158 --> 00:07:41,160
Hey, listen, I was taking
a creative writing course...

91
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,528
one time in community college.

92
00:07:42,528 --> 00:07:44,497
I'll help you with it
on my off night.

93
00:07:44,497 --> 00:07:45,998
We'll get together,
we'll rewrite the thing.

94
00:07:45,998 --> 00:07:47,533
Those things don't work.

95
00:07:47,533 --> 00:07:50,536
I got one more inside
we got to get.

96
00:07:50,536 --> 00:07:53,937
So, yeah, we'll just get
together, like, Wednesday night.

97
00:08:01,948 --> 00:08:03,506
What's that smell?

98
00:08:05,451 --> 00:08:07,783
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

99
00:08:08,955 --> 00:08:11,290
Shoot it. Shoot it.

100
00:08:11,290 --> 00:08:12,416
OK.

101
00:08:14,861 --> 00:08:16,629
I don't eat doughnuts all day.

102
00:08:16,629 --> 00:08:18,998
I eat doughnuts in the evening.
I eat candy bars in the morning.

103
00:08:18,998 --> 00:08:21,667
Listen, you should try driving
with this shit in your trunk.

104
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:22,835
You ever get a whiff
of this shit?

105
00:08:22,835 --> 00:08:25,071
It stinks.
I'll buy you some air freshener.

106
00:08:25,071 --> 00:08:26,197
How do you like that?

107
00:08:39,986 --> 00:08:41,988
This must be the place.

108
00:08:41,988 --> 00:08:44,257
Got everything?

109
00:08:44,257 --> 00:08:46,350
Have I ever forgotten anything
before?

110
00:08:49,395 --> 00:08:50,521
Let's do it.

111
00:08:55,968 --> 00:08:57,560
Oh, my God.

112
00:09:03,743 --> 00:09:06,012
Look at this. Look at this.
Annie, tape the rabbit.

113
00:09:06,012 --> 00:09:07,280
Got it, got it, got it.

114
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,872
Hey, pan down the row.

115
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:13,219
Look. They took her ear off.

116
00:09:13,219 --> 00:09:15,888
Move in on this one. This one.

117
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:17,856
Look at the size of this wound.

118
00:09:19,058 --> 00:09:22,161
Now pull back and get the name
of this monkey.

119
00:09:22,161 --> 00:09:25,064
OK, stay out of the shot.

120
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:27,733
These people are sick. Look.

121
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:29,702
Look at her head.

122
00:09:29,702 --> 00:09:31,804
And the tattoo on her face, too.

123
00:09:31,804 --> 00:09:34,034
This is unbelievable.

124
00:09:35,675 --> 00:09:38,477
- Bring your camera up here.
- Hold on, I'm coming.

125
00:09:38,477 --> 00:09:40,913
Look at this place.
Look at this place.

126
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:43,883
We've got to get this whole shot
of the whole place.

127
00:09:43,883 --> 00:09:47,153
I want people to really see
what's going on in here.

128
00:09:47,153 --> 00:09:49,621
What kind of person
could do all this?

129
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:53,991
- Fifty-five, dude.
- Yeah, yeah.

130
00:09:57,997 --> 00:09:59,999
Did he take everything, Manning?

131
00:09:59,999 --> 00:10:01,200
Yes, sir, Dr. Jarret.

132
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:03,169
Meet me around back.
I got some specimens...

133
00:10:03,169 --> 00:10:04,796
I want you to help me
take up to the lab.

134
00:10:07,773 --> 00:10:08,899
Damn.

135
00:10:15,581 --> 00:10:17,742
I'm not so sure about this.

136
00:10:20,853 --> 00:10:24,690
Oh, no. Look at this.

137
00:10:24,690 --> 00:10:26,525
Do we have enough light
to tape in here?

138
00:10:26,525 --> 00:10:28,027
Yeah, it's good.

139
00:10:28,027 --> 00:10:30,029
I can't believe
they're experimenting...

140
00:10:30,029 --> 00:10:32,632
on endangered species
like these.

141
00:10:32,632 --> 00:10:35,134
This is really strange.

142
00:10:35,134 --> 00:10:37,203
I'm not even sure
if this is legal.

143
00:10:37,203 --> 00:10:40,104
Annie, Annie, look at the bear.

144
00:10:44,410 --> 00:10:45,578
Come on, come on.
What are you waiting for?

145
00:10:45,578 --> 00:10:46,879
Be there in a second, doctor.

146
00:10:46,879 --> 00:10:48,381
Get the other cage.

147
00:10:48,381 --> 00:10:50,349
Get these doors here open.

148
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:10,770
This is a major piece.

149
00:11:10,770 --> 00:11:13,639
We have got a real story.
This is going to work.

150
00:11:13,639 --> 00:11:14,807
Lori.

151
00:11:14,807 --> 00:11:16,642
What's in here?
Did you see what was in here?

152
00:11:16,642 --> 00:11:18,344
Let's just get out of here.

153
00:11:18,344 --> 00:11:21,836
Here we have a rare, extinct...

154
00:11:23,716 --> 00:11:25,308
dog.

155
00:11:29,889 --> 00:11:31,791
Let me get that for you, doctor.

156
00:11:31,791 --> 00:11:34,527
Take these
and put them in the lab.

157
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:35,653
Thank you.

158
00:11:40,599 --> 00:11:43,235
What are they
doing to you, huh?

159
00:11:43,235 --> 00:11:44,725
I don't think
you should be doing that.

160
00:11:46,038 --> 00:11:49,041
I want to check him out.
He's not going to do anything.

161
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:51,210
Hey, what are they doing to you
around here, huh?

162
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:53,312
Poor little guy.

163
00:11:53,312 --> 00:11:56,682
Don't you look at me.
I didn't put you in there.

164
00:11:56,682 --> 00:12:00,152
You were probably a lawyer
in another life, I bet.

165
00:12:00,152 --> 00:12:03,622
What is this thing
they have on him?

166
00:12:03,622 --> 00:12:07,793
What is this?
What are these wires?

167
00:12:07,793 --> 00:12:09,693
Your rooms are ready.

168
00:12:12,098 --> 00:12:14,433
Wake-up call's at 6:00.

169
00:12:14,433 --> 00:12:17,737
You can check in,
but you can't check out.

170
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:20,673
- Do you have us both in frame?
- Yeah, why?

171
00:12:20,673 --> 00:12:22,408
I want to do
the intro to the story.

172
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:24,310
Are you crazy?
We can do that later.

173
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:26,540
No, it's perfect now. Now.

174
00:12:34,253 --> 00:12:35,354
Do I look OK?

175
00:12:35,354 --> 00:12:37,720
- You look beautiful. Hurry up.
- Dog slobber!

176
00:12:43,996 --> 00:12:45,331
Rolling.

177
00:12:45,331 --> 00:12:47,666
Is this dog
really a noble sacrifice...

178
00:12:47,666 --> 00:12:50,970
donating his life
for the betterment of mankind...

179
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:53,038
or is he simply
an innocent victim...

180
00:12:53,038 --> 00:12:56,442
of the billion-dollar
vivisection industry?

181
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:59,311
Shit. Shit. Doggie!

182
00:12:59,311 --> 00:13:00,946
Max! Max!

183
00:13:00,946 --> 00:13:02,413
Get back here.

184
00:13:04,483 --> 00:13:05,718
- Max!
- Where did he go?

185
00:13:05,718 --> 00:13:06,886
Max?

186
00:13:06,886 --> 00:13:09,455
Hey! Hey, hold it right there!

187
00:13:09,455 --> 00:13:11,923
Hey, hold it!
Hold it right there! Stop!

188
00:13:17,997 --> 00:13:19,464
Shit!

189
00:13:21,834 --> 00:13:25,104
- Hurry!
- I'm trying! Go! Go!

190
00:13:25,104 --> 00:13:27,072
- Jesus!
- Shit!

191
00:13:27,072 --> 00:13:29,472
What the hell
are you doing here?

192
00:13:32,478 --> 00:13:34,780
Max.

193
00:13:34,780 --> 00:13:36,270
What's going on?

194
00:13:37,316 --> 00:13:39,151
What are you doing out?

195
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:40,982
Sit.

196
00:13:44,723 --> 00:13:45,849
Max.

197
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:49,118
Halt, Max.

198
00:13:51,964 --> 00:13:53,522
Good boy. Good boy.

199
00:13:57,336 --> 00:13:58,838
Max, you're scaring me.

200
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:00,772
I'm not angry with you.
I'm just tired.

201
00:14:01,941 --> 00:14:03,275
Max...

202
00:14:03,275 --> 00:14:05,411
final command.

203
00:14:05,411 --> 00:14:07,003
Enter.

204
00:14:12,017 --> 00:14:13,541
Enter.

205
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:17,256
Max...

206
00:14:17,256 --> 00:14:18,382
Max.

207
00:14:21,994 --> 00:14:23,222
Now.

208
00:14:25,931 --> 00:14:27,125
Max!

209
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,002
Max!

210
00:14:30,002 --> 00:14:32,664
God damn it!

211
00:14:44,183 --> 00:14:46,879
- Where's the car?
- Over there.

212
00:15:10,476 --> 00:15:13,001
Come on, come on! What are you
waiting for? Let's go!

213
00:15:14,413 --> 00:15:16,081
Just get in!
Just get in the car.

214
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:17,249
You don't know
what you're doing!

215
00:15:17,249 --> 00:15:19,251
Get in!

216
00:15:19,251 --> 00:15:21,151
Forget the dog!

217
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:24,780
Max! No!

218
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:30,296
Oh, man! Oh, man! Sucker!

219
00:15:30,296 --> 00:15:32,765
Max!

220
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:34,357
No!

221
00:15:35,501 --> 00:15:38,470
Max! Max!

222
00:15:40,172 --> 00:15:42,308
You said they had
a video camera.

223
00:15:42,308 --> 00:15:44,333
Any idea why?

224
00:15:46,512 --> 00:15:48,013
About six months ago...

225
00:15:48,013 --> 00:15:51,016
there was a group
of animal rights fanatics...

226
00:15:51,016 --> 00:15:53,786
protesting outside the lab.

227
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:54,954
I called the police.

228
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:56,288
A couple of 'em
tried to break in.

229
00:15:56,288 --> 00:15:57,856
Maybe that's the connection.

230
00:15:57,856 --> 00:15:59,692
Emilio, why don't you see
if we booked anyone?

231
00:15:59,692 --> 00:16:03,423
Nah, nah, nah, nah.
The police did nothing.

232
00:16:05,664 --> 00:16:07,466
Exactly what kind of work
do you do here?

233
00:16:07,466 --> 00:16:09,702
I do genetic research...

234
00:16:09,702 --> 00:16:12,304
often using animal models.

235
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:14,239
You talking about vivisection?

236
00:16:14,239 --> 00:16:15,741
Yes, I am.

237
00:16:15,741 --> 00:16:16,909
Vivi what?

238
00:16:16,909 --> 00:16:18,510
Vivisection...

239
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:20,512
those cruel experiments
they do on animals...

240
00:16:20,512 --> 00:16:21,981
to test out new products.

241
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:24,850
My girlfriend talks about it
all the time.

242
00:16:24,850 --> 00:16:28,554
She wants to make sure
things like the shampoo I use...

243
00:16:28,554 --> 00:16:30,923
are on a cruelty-free
products list.

244
00:16:30,923 --> 00:16:32,558
Well, your girlfriend
is rather ignorant...

245
00:16:32,558 --> 00:16:35,561
like most of these
animal rights people.

246
00:16:35,561 --> 00:16:37,096
You try telling her that.

247
00:16:37,096 --> 00:16:39,531
Look. The kind of research
I do here...

248
00:16:39,531 --> 00:16:43,002
is about saving lives,
human lives.

249
00:16:43,002 --> 00:16:45,004
That's what's important,
isn't it?

250
00:16:45,004 --> 00:16:47,406
I don't make eyeliner here...

251
00:16:47,406 --> 00:16:49,508
and I don't pour acid
into monkeys' eyes...

252
00:16:49,508 --> 00:16:51,176
or stitch them closed, either.

253
00:16:51,176 --> 00:16:53,912
We get the picture, doc.
We'll be in touch.

254
00:16:53,912 --> 00:16:56,015
Yeah.

255
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:57,850
I want Max back.

256
00:16:57,850 --> 00:17:00,619
We're not talking about
a street mutt here.

257
00:17:00,619 --> 00:17:01,787
